      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black, featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This power unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system to produce a sharp, linear power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. Crucial preventative maintenance has been addressed: the rear subframe has been reinforced with plates, and the VANOS unit has been overhauled with upgraded seals and a cryo-treated hub. The chassis remains taut with refreshed bushings and OE-spec dampers, providing the precise turn-in and communicative feedback these cars are known for. While the aesthetic condition shows minor road-going patina, the mechanical synchronization and thermal management are excellent, making this a driver-focused example ready for the twisties.",
